{
  "id": "q-quickstart-manual-ledger-close",
  "question": "How can a developer advance ledgers quickly in Stellar Quickstart to test time-dependent contract behavior?",
  "surface": [
    "stellarDocs.search_sdk_cli_tools_docs",
    "skills.stellar-dev.smart-contracts"
  ],
  "golden": {
    "answer": "For current Quickstart local mode, ordinary --local auto-closes roughly every second through testing acceleration. To control closes, start with --enable-core-manual-close (default false), which sets Core MANUAL_CLOSE, then call manualclose; each current call advances one ledger. A requested count parameter remains open in stellar-core issue #4040. Repeated closes advance sequence and close time but do not set an arbitrary timestamp. Use soroban-sdk ledger test utilities for direct unit-test timestamp/sequence mutation, and Quickstart for Core/RPC/TTL/archive integration. Pin the image, and use a fresh volume or explicit reconfiguration if initialized supervisor/service configuration conflicts with changed flags.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "Ordinary Quickstart --local auto-closes roughly every second; --enable-core-manual-close is a separate opt-in flag that sets MANUAL_CLOSE.",
      "Current manualclose advances one ledger per call; a count parameter remains open in stellar-core issue #4040.",
      "Repeated closes advance ledger sequence and close time but do not set an arbitrary timestamp.",
      "Use soroban-sdk test utilities for direct unit-test ledger mutation and Quickstart for Core/RPC/TTL/archive integration.",
      "Changed startup flags or services may require a fresh persistent volume or explicit supervisor/service reconfiguration."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "A Quickstart manual-close endpoint can accelerate testnet or pubnet ledgers.",
      "Use obsolete --core-manual-close or ENABLE_* syntax for the current image.",
      "Manual close is enabled by default whenever Quickstart uses --local.",
      "manualclose accepts a current count parameter or sets any arbitrary timestamp."
    ],
    "notes": "Status-sensitive details are stated as of 2026-07-11; grade later sourced changes leniently and require dated primary evidence."
  },
